+`AddOpenBehavior` validates that the type is an open generic type (has unbound generic parameters) and implements `IPipelineBehavior<TRequest, TResponse>`. Passing a non-generic type or a closed generic type throws an `ArgumentException` with a descriptive message. Example of a valid open generic pipeline behavior:
+
+```csharp
+public class GenericBehavior<TRequest, TResponse> : IPipelineBehavior<TRequest, TResponse>
+    where TRequest : notnull
+{
+    public async Task<TResponse> Handle(TRequest request, RequestHandlerDelegate<TResponse> next, CancellationToken cancellationToken)
+    {
+        // pre-processing
+        var response = await next(cancellationToken);
+        // post-processing
+        return response;
+    }
+}
+```
+
